 Webhook Dispatcher Response Handling**: The `callHook()` method in validating/dispatcher.go:\n   - Calls the webhook via REST client\n   - Verifies the admission response\n   - Extracts audit annotations and warnings\n   - Returns rejection error if webhook denies the request\n   - Parallel calls are aggregated with the first error being returned\n\n## Supporting Components\n\n1. **WebhookAccessor** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go`): Provides a unified interface for accessing mutating and validating webhook configurations. Implements caching for compiled matchers and REST clients.\n\n2. **Error Handling** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/errors/statuserror.go`): The `ToStatusErr()` function converts webhook rejections to proper Kubernetes status errors.\n\n3. **Configuration Managers**:\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/mutating_webhook_manager.go`: Manages MutatingWebhookConfiguration objects\n   - `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/validating_webhook_manager.go`: Manages ValidatingWebhookConfiguration objects\n\n4. **Initializer** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/initializer/initializer.go`): Initializes webhook plugins with necessary dependencies.\n\n5. **Match Conditions** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/matchconditions/matcher.go`): Handles CEL-based match conditions for webhook invocation filtering.\n\n6. **Reinvocation Context** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/reinvocationcontext.go`): Manages webhook reinvocation for mutating webhooks when mutations change the request object.\n\n## Call Flow Summary\n\n1. API server calls `Admit()` (mutating) or `Validate()` (validating) on the plugin\n2. Plugin delegates to `Webhook.Dispatch()`\n3. `Dispatch()` checks if webhooks should be called and retrieves the webhook list\n4. Dispatcher's `Dispatch()` is called with the hook list\n5. For each matching hook, the dispatcher calls the webhook via REST client\n6. `CreateAdmissionObjects()` creates the AdmissionReview request\n7. Webhook response is verified with `VerifyAdmissionResponse()`\n8. For mutating webhooks: patches are applied and mutations are tracked\n9. For validating webhooks: multiple calls are made in parallel and errors are aggregated\n10. Final decision and audit annotations are returned to the API server"
